# Deploy after work (NovaPredict)

When you finish a task that changed code (not question-only / review-only turns), **deploy the app before you stop**.

## Canonical command

Run from `app/`:

```bash
npm run deploy:cf:full
```

This executes `scripts/deploy-cloudflare-locally.sh`: `wrangler whoami` → `npm ci` → `npm run lint` → `npm run build:cf` → `npm run deploy:cf`.

## Fast path (same session)

If you already ran `npm run lint` and `npm run build:cf` successfully in this session:

```bash
npm run deploy:cf:full:fast
```

Equivalent to `--skip-install --skip-tests`.

## Do not

- Do **not** use bare `npm run deploy:cf` as the default finish step — use the full script so lint/build run first.
- Do **not** assume Vercel or Cloudflare Pages git deploy — production is **Workers via OpenNext** only.

## When to skip app deploy

Skip only for **read-only** answers or changes limited to `pipeline/`, root docs, or `.env.example` with **zero** `app/` impact. If `app/` changed, always deploy.

## On failure

1. Read `app/tmp/deploy-cloudflare-local-latest.log`
2. Fix the failing step (lint, build, wrangler auth, etc.)
3. Re-run `npm run deploy:cf:full` (or `:fast` if install/lint already passed)

Production URL: `https://novapredict.buildngrowsv.workers.dev`

Requires `wrangler login` on the machine running deploy.
